---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Framer AI Review: Visual Builder Worth It? (2025)',
  description: 'Honest Framer AI review. Best for designers who want visual control with AI assistance. Pricing, pros/cons, and when to choose alternatives.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Framer AI review', 'Framer pricing', 'AI website builder', 'Framer vs Webflow', 'Framer vs WordPress'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Tested · Honest · No Hype
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Framer AI Review: Visual Builder Worth It?
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Framer sits between Durable's speed and v0.dev's code ownership. Visual builder with AI features. Great for designers, annoying for developers. Here's the honest truth.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: <AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink> wins for designers who want visual control with AI assistance. Not for developers (use <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>). Not for non-technical (use <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>). Sweet spot: designers who can code a little.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          $5-30/month. Can export code but it's messy. You're mostly locked in. Best for marketing sites and landing pages where visual polish matters more than perfect code.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Framer Does -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Framer AI Actually Does
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">Core approach: Visual builder with AI features</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer is primarily a visual website builder (like Webflow but more modern). You drag-and-drop elements, style them visually, see changes in real-time. AI features generate sections or pages when you want them, but you can also design everything manually.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">AI generation features</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Text generation:</strong> Describe your page, AI writes copy</li>
          <li>• <strong>Section generation:</strong> Generate hero sections, features, testimonials</li>
          <li>• <strong>Full pages:</strong> Create complete landing pages from prompts</li>
          <li>• <strong>Image suggestions:</strong> AI suggests relevant images from Unsplash</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">Manual design features</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Visual editor:</strong> Drag-and-drop like Figma for web</li>
          <li>• <strong>Responsive design:</strong> Mobile, tablet, desktop breakpoints</li>
          <li>• <strong>Animations:</strong> Built-in micro-interactions and transitions</li>
          <li>• <strong>CMS integration:</strong> Blog, portfolio, dynamic content</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">Export capability</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">You CAN export your Framer site as React code. This is the big selling point vs Webflow. But the exported code is not clean. It's not meant for production deployment. Think of export as a backup, not a migration path.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Framer Pricing (January 2025)
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Mini -->
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-xl text-gray-900">Mini</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Personal projects</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-green-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-bold">$5/mo</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>✓ 1 published site</li>
          <li>✓ Framer branding</li>
          <li>✓ Unlimited pages</li>
          <li>✓ Basic CMS</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Plus -->
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-xl text-gray-900">Plus (Annual)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Professionals and freelancers</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-purple-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-bold">$15/mo</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>✓ 3 published sites</li>
          <li>✓ Custom domain</li>
          <li>✓ Remove Framer branding</li>
          <li>✓ Advanced CMS</li>
          <li>✓ SEO features</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://framer.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg">
          Start Free Trial
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Pro -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-xl text-gray-900">Pro (Annual)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Advanced users</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-bold">$30/mo</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>✓ 10 published sites</li>
          <li>✓ Everything in Plus</li>
          <li>✓ Custom code</li>
          <li>✓ Analytics</li>
          <li>✓ Priority support</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://framer.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg">
          Get Pro
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 mt-6">
      <p class="font-black mb-2">Annual billing saves ~25%</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Plus: $15/mo annually ($180/year) vs $20/mo monthly ($240/year). Pro: $30/mo annually ($360/year) vs $40/mo monthly ($480/year). Annual billing saves $60-120/year.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Framer Does Well -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Where Framer Wins
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Visual control without coding</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer's drag-and-drop interface is excellent. If you think visually, you'll love designing in Framer. Move elements with your mouse, adjust spacing visually, see changes instantly. Much faster than coding for many designers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ AI when you want it, not forced</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Unlike Durable where AI generates everything, Framer lets you choose. Design manually when you have a vision. Use AI for boring parts (generating testimonials section, writing about text). Best of both worlds.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Animations and micro-interactions</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer excels at animations. Hover states, scroll effects, page transitions. Add these with clicks, not code. Makes sites feel polished and professional. Marketing sites come alive with these details.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Better than Webflow for most people</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Webflow is powerful but has a learning cliff. Framer is more intuitive. Faster to learn. Easier to use. AI features add speed. If you're choosing between Webflow and Framer, start with Framer.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ React-based (modern stack)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer generates React code under the hood. This is modern, future-proof technology. Unlike WordPress's PHP mess or Squarespace's black box. If you export, you get actual React (just messy).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Framer Does Poorly -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Where Framer Loses
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">❌ Export is messy (not production-ready)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, you can export code. No, it's not clean. The exported React has unnecessary wrappers, weird class names, dependencies you don't need. Works for backup, not for serious deployment. You're mostly locked in.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">❌ Monthly subscription forever</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Stop paying, lose your site. $15-30/month forever. Year 1: $180-360. Year 5: $900-1,800. That's expensive for a static site. If you own the code, hosting costs $5/month or free on <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">❌ Not for complex applications</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer is for marketing sites, landing pages, portfolios. Not for SaaS apps, not for e-commerce, not for complex dashboards. If you need backend logic, user auth, database — wrong tool. Use <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> + Next.js instead.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">❌ Developers find it limiting</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">If you know React/Next.js, Framer feels limiting. You want to write code, Framer wants you to click things. You want clean components, Framer gives you nested divs. Developers prefer <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> for direct code control.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">❌ Learning curve for non-designers</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer is easier than Webflow but still has a learning curve. If you have zero design sense, you'll struggle. Spacing, typography, color theory — Framer doesn't teach you. <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink> is better if you just want a site fast.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Framer vs Alternatives
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">vs <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink></h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> Visual builder, designers love it, monthly subscription, export is messy.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>v0.dev:</strong> Code-first, developers love it, free tier, full code ownership.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Framer if:</strong> You're a designer who wants visual control.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose v0.dev if:</strong> You're a developer who wants clean code and ownership.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">vs <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink></h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> Visual control, 30-60 min build time, more customization.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Durable:</strong> AI generates everything, 30-second build, less control.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Framer if:</strong> You care about design and customization.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Durable if:</strong> You want a site fast and don't care about details.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">vs Webflow</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> Easier to learn, AI features, more modern, cheaper.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Webflow:</strong> More powerful, larger community, more established.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Framer if:</strong> You're starting fresh and want something modern.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Webflow if:</strong> You need advanced features or rely on Webflow University.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">vs WordPress</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> Modern, fast, visual builder, $15-30/mo.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>WordPress:</strong> Old but powerful, plugin ecosystem, cheaper hosting.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Framer if:</strong> Building a marketing site and want modern experience.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose WordPress if:</strong> You need plugins, blogging features, or want full control.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Should Use Framer -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Who Should Use Framer?
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Perfect For:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Designers:</strong> Visual workflow matches how you think</li>
          <li>• <strong>Marketing sites:</strong> Landing pages, product launches, portfolios</li>
          <li>• <strong>Freelancers:</strong> Fast client work with polished output</li>
          <li>• <strong>Webflow refugees:</strong> Want something easier and more modern</li>
          <li>• <strong>People who can code a little:</strong> Not intimidated by technical concepts</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">❌ Not For:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Developers:</strong> You'll hate the visual workflow, use <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink></li>
          <li>• <strong>Non-technical users:</strong> Learning curve, use <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink></li>
          <li>• <strong>Complex apps:</strong> SaaS, e-commerce, dashboards need custom code</li>
          <li>• <strong>Code purists:</strong> Export is messy, you're locked in</li>
          <li>• <strong>Budget-conscious:</strong> $15-30/mo forever adds up</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Framer is the Goldilocks option:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• <strong>More control than Durable</strong> — Visual builder, AI optional</li>
        <li>• <strong>Easier than v0.dev</strong> — No coding required (but possible)</li>
        <li>• <strong>More modern than Webflow</strong> — Better UX, AI features</li>
        <li>• <strong>Less lock-in than Squarespace</strong> — Can export (even if messy)</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Best use case: Marketing sites and landing pages where visual polish matters, you care about design, and you're comfortable with some technical concepts.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Worst use case: Complex applications, non-technical users who just want a site, developers who want clean code ownership.</p>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 mt-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">My recommendation:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Try Framer's free trial. Build a landing page. See if the visual workflow clicks for you. If it feels intuitive, you've found your tool. If it feels frustrating, you're either too technical (use <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>) or not technical enough (use <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Reality Check -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Reality Check
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2">Framer Plus: $180/year</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Year 1: $180. Year 5: $900. That's real money.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>: Free</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Year 1: $0. Year 5: $0 (assuming <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> free tier). You own the code.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>: $180-360/year</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Similar to Framer. But Durable generates sites in 30 seconds, not 30 minutes. Less control, faster output.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2">The math:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">If you're building marketing sites professionally, Framer Plus pays for itself with one client project. If it's a personal site, $180/year is expensive for what you get. Consider whether the visual workflow is worth $180/year vs. free alternatives.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related AI Builder Guides
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/durable-ai-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable AI Full Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">30-second website generation</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/durable-vs-v0-vs-framer" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable vs v0 vs Framer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Which AI builder wins?</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
